    "macroSummary": "Markets are experiencing risk-on rotation driven by Middle East peace deal optimism, with oil falling below $100 and equity futures rising as 'war trade' positions unwind. However, underlying structural weakness persists with crypto volumes down 39% in Q1, Bitcoin miners selling record amounts, and technical levels showing mixed signals with BTC rejected at $76K despite some institutional buying.",
