    "actionItems": [
      "Maintain BMNR cash-secured put ladder as BTC shows rejection at $76K but remains above $62,300 structural level with BlackRock still accumulating",
      "Consider reducing short book exposure on war trade unwind and risk-on rotation into growth names like NVDA and NFLX",
      "Hold Maturity sector overweight as 10Y yields holding advance suggests growth stress persists despite temporary relief rally"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil falling below $100 removes stagflation risk and supports risk assets in near term.",
      "BTC rejection at $76K with whale inflows exploding suggests distribution at resistance levels.",
      "Dollar weakness for second straight week on Iran peace optimism supports risk asset relief rally.",
      "Crypto winter deepening with 39% CEX volume decline contradicts surface-level BTC strength narrative."
